Lives","peeks":"Peeks","round":"Round","score":"Score","across":"Across","streak":"Streak","hotkeys":"Hotkeys","see_all":"See All","top_one":"Top 1","top_two":"Top 2","attempts":"Attempts","crossword":"Crossword","easy_mode":"Easy Mode","goto_game":"Go to the %\{type\} game","next_word":"Next Word","see_score":"See Score","top_three":"Top 3","categories":"Categories","snake_game":"Snake Game","win_streak":"Win streak","card_hunter":\{"first_instructions":"The object of the game is to match one pair of related terms each round. The first round starts with 4 cards showing. Two of the cards will be from the same flashcard (side 1 and side 2), the other two cards will be random. It is your job to choose the 2 cards from the same flashcard. If you choose the two correct cards, you will move on to the next round. If you fail to match the cards, you will lose a life and restart the round. Two additional cards will be added each round you complete successfully. Try to pass as many rounds as you can and get the highest score. Points are earned for successful pairings based on how fast you select the correct cards and the round you are on. Good luck!","second_instructions":"The object of the game is to match one pair of related terms. The number of cards you will see depends on level of difficulty set. Among all the cards you will see there will be two from the same flashcard (side 1 and side 2), the other cards will be random. It is your job to choose the 2 cards from the same flashcard. If you choose the two correct cards, you will be rewarded by the score based on how fast you picked those cards and level of difficulty set. If you fail to match the cards, you will lose a life. Feel free to change difficulty as you see fit and get the highest score. Good luck!"\},"card_picker":"Card Picker","play_button":"Play","take_a_peek":"Take a peek","total_score":"Total score %\{score\}","card_coupler":"Card Coupler","card_flipped":"Card flipped","card_sweeper":"Card Sweeper","current_word":"current word","leaderboards":"Leaderboards","sudden_death":"Sudden Death","answer_streak":"Answer Streak","highest_score":"Your highest score","new_crossword":"New Crossword","pause_control":"Pause control","previous_word":"Previous Word","start_playing":"Start playing","card_hunter_one":"Card Hunter I","card_hunter_two":"Card Hunter II","flashcard_games":\{"sads1":"Try again!","sads2":"Tough luck! Try again!","sads3":"Bummer! Try again!","sads4":"You can do better!","sads5":"Sad panda!","sads6":"Ouch! Maybe next time!","cheers1":"Good job!","cheers2":"Well done!","cheers3":"Not bad!","cheers4":"Wicked try!","cheers5":"Nice results!","cheers6":"Cool! Try again!","cheers7":"Happy camper!","cheers8":"Sweet!","cheers9":"Well played!","cheers10":"You nailed it!","you_ran_out":"Sorry, you ran out of cards. Play again."\},"lives_remaining":"You have %\{lives\} lives remaining","pause_to_review":"Pause to review","select_category":"Select category","this_is_correct":"This is correct.","top_game_scores":"Top Game Scores","your_best_score":"Your Best Score","i_am_done_button":"I'm done","submit_crossword":"Submit Crossword","card_hunter_title":"Card Hunter","correctness_label":"This match is %\{correctnessLabel\}.","crossword_hotkeys":\{"end":"End","tab":"Tab","home":"Home","spacebar":"Spacebar","backspace":"Backspace","next_word":"Next word","arrow_keys":"Arrow keys","previous_word":"Previous word","shift_plus_tab":"Shift + Tab","go_to_last_letter":"Go to last letter in word","go_to_first_letter":"Go to first letter in word","move_current_letter":"Move current letter","clear_current_letter":"Clear current letter","toggle_word_direction":"Toggle word direction","crossword_keyboard_shortcuts":"Crossword Keyboard Shortcuts"\},"play_card_coupler":"Play the card couple","this_is_incorrect":"This is incorrect. The correct answer was %\{correctAnswer\}","all_sub_categories":"All Subcategories","highest_win_streak":"Highest win streak %\{maxCount\}","not_yet_determined":"Not yet determined","reveal_correct_word":"Reveal Current Word","select_sub_category":"Select subcategory","easy_mode_instruction":"Easy Mode automatically highlights incorrect letters in red. The highest possible score will be lower in easy mode.","reveal_current_letter":"Reveal Current Letter","submit_your_crossword":"Submit your completed crossword","crossword_instructions":"The object of this game is to fill in the crossword using the clues provided for each word. Points are earned based on how fast you complete the crossword, how many words you get correct, and how many hints you use. Good luck!","discard_your_crossword":"Discard your current progress and generate a new crossword","reveal_the_correct_word":"Reveal the correct word (this will decrease your score)","your_answered_correctly":"You answered correctly.","card_picker_instructions":"The object of the game is to correctly match Side 1 of the flashcard with Side 2.  Each turn, a different term from Side 1 of the flashcard will show and 6 possible matches will be listed below.  It is your job to choose the correct Side 2 from the 6 possible matches.  Points are earned for successful pairings based on how fast you select the correct card.  Good luck!","no_high_score_to_display":"No high scores to display","restart_card_hunter_game":"Restart the card hunter game","this_match_correct_label":"This match is %\{correctLabel\}.","card_coupler_instructions":"The object of the game is to match 8 pairs of cards. At the start of the game, you will be shown side 1 and side 2 of eight flashcards. Upon clicking play, all of the cards will be turned over and jumbled up in random order. It is your job to remember side 1 and side 2 of each flashcard as well as their location on the board. If you successfully pair 2 cards, they will be removed from the board. If you fail to pair 2 cards, they will be flipped back over. The game is over when all eight pairs are matched. You can take a peek at the cards by clicking on the eye and all cards will be turned over and shown for 10 seconds. For each time you peek you will lose points in the final score. Points are earned based on how fast you pair the cards and the number of attempts. Good luck!","card_sweeper_instructions":"The object of the game is to match all cards on the board. At the start of the game, you will be shown 8 cards. Of those 8 cards, there is 1 successful match. If you pair side 1 and side 2 of the match correctly, those cards will disappear and the board will jumble in a different order with an additional 1 card. Of those 7 cards (6 existing, 1 new), there is a new successful match to be found. If you pair side 1 and side 2 of the new match correctly, those cards will disappear and the same thing will happen but with 6 cards.  If you continue to match all the cards successfully, your board will be blank at which point YOU WIN THE GAME.  Now, if you pair side 1 and side 2 incorrectly, the board will re-jumble and 2 additional cards will be added.  Of those 10 cards (8 existing, 2 new), there are 2 successful matches to be found. If you continue to match cards incorrectly, the board will add 2 cards until it is full, at which point you lose the game.","reveal_the_correct_letter":"Reveal the correct letter (this will decrease your score)","sudden_death_instructions":"The object of the game is to answer as many questions in a row as possible. You can choose both the category and subcategory if you want to focus on a particular knowledge area. Good luck!","flashcard_set_is_not_available":"Flashcard set is not available for Crossword","restart_card_picker_area_label":"Restart the card picker game","restart_card_sweeper_aria_label":"Restart the card sweeper game"\},"simulations":\{"done":"Done","error":\{"text":"Sorry, failed to capture results for %\{id\}. Please try again.","title":"Problem with simulation"\},"correct":"Correct","tooltip":"This is the average score of all completed simulations in this product.","dashboard":\{"st