:"Practice Question Prompt","response_override_update_success":"Successfully published Response Message Overrides","reading_section_prompt_placeholder":"Task Prompt"\},"strictness":\{"title":"Response Guardrails","subtitle":"By default, the AI Assistant will keep its answers very strictly limited to information it can find directly stated in your product content. If desired, you can adjust the guardrails to include more of the LLM\'92s generic training information.","low_label":"No Product Data Restriction","card_title":"Referential Source Guardrails","high_label":"Strictly Product Content Only (Default)","low_example":"Example: A learner is in a product about Geometry which only includes content specifically about mathematical concepts. The learner asks \'93What makes the sky blue?\'94 The AI Assistant will answer this question, providing a general scientific explanation from its training data, despite the question having no relation to the product content.","save_button":"Publish Response Guardrails","high_example":"Example: A learner is in a product about Geometry which only includes content specifically about mathematical concepts. The learner asks \'93How could I become a Geometry teacher?\'94 The AI Assistant will not answer this question, as your product has no content about pursuing a career in Geometry.","medium_label":"Some Extrapolation Allowed","update_error":"An unknown error occurred while updating Response Guardrails","medium_example":"Example: A learner is in a product about Geometry which only includes content specifically about mathematical concepts. The learner asks \'93How could I become a Geometry teacher?\'94 The AI Assistant will answer this question, given it is somewhat related to the product, and will likely recommend certain areas of focus and skills to develop based on its generic training data.","update_success":"Response Guardrails published successfully","low_description":"Choose this option if you\'92d like the AI Assistant to make full use of the LLM\'92s generic training data, including providing answers to questions that are unrelated to the learner\'92s product. While able to answer the widest range of learner questions, please note this also comes with the possibility of the AI Assistant providing answers that may deviate from, or even contradict, your product content.","high_description":"Choose this option if you want the AI Assistant responses to only include answers that are directly stated in your imported product content. The AI Assistant will make no logical leaps or extrapolations, even when learner questions are related to topics in your product.","medium_description":"Choose this option if you\'92d like the AI Assistant to be able to make some logical inferences and extrapolations based on your product content. The AI Assistant will still keep conversations restricted to topics in your product, but may pull from the LLM\'92s generic training data to fill in gaps or make inferences on user questions that are not answered directly by your product content.","confirmation_dialog_text":"Clicking \\"Confirm\\" will immediately update the Configuration","confirmation_dialog_title":"Publish?","confirmation_dialog_button":"Confirm"\},"feature_tab_label":"Features","branding_tab_label":"Branding","messaging_tab_label":"Messaging","referential_sources":\{"header":"Referential Sources","description":"This is a listing of all the courses that have been ingested by the AI making them available to either host the AI assistant or act as a helper product. A product must be ingested to have the AI assistant available. Use manage to add additional courses.","manage_button":"Manage","content_package_title":"Product Name"\},"ai_tutor_upsell_copy":"AI Assistant currently is not enabled for your organization. Please reach out to your CSM to enable this functionality.","strictness_tab_label":"Response Guardrails","manage_referential_sources":\{"header":"Manage Referential Sources","subtitle_1":"Adding co