<div class="modal-inner">\
  <div class="modal-header">\
    <h1 class="title">\
      <strong>Interpreting My Results</strong>\
    </h1>\
  </div>\
  <div class="modal-body">\
    \
      <p>\
        Practice question products allow you to use MCAT style questions to gauge your progress in mastering the content measured by the MCAT exam. See <a href="https://students-residents.aamc.org/prepare-mcat-exam/creating-your-mcat-exam-study-plan" target="_blank">Creating your MCAT Exam Study Plan <span class="sr-only">Opens in new window</span></a> for tips on how to use practice questions as part of an effective study and practice cycle.\
      </p>\
    \
    \
    <span class="header underlined">Reviewing Results</span>\
    <p>\
      \
        The Question Review screen allows you to understand each question and view the solution. The Content and Skills Breakdown section allows you to see how you performed in each foundational concept, content category, skill, and discipline. The higher the number of questions taken in a given content and skill area, the more reflective it is of your performance in that area. Learn more about the content and skills tested by seeing how questions are categorized in the <a href="https://students-residents.aamc.org/prepare-mcat-exam/whats-mcat-exam" target="_blank">What\'92s on the MCAT Exam? Content Outline. <span class="sr-only">Opens in new window</span></a>\
      \
    </p>\
  </div>\
</div>\
</div><div class="interpret-results-modal modal fade" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true" style="display: none;"><a aria-label="Dismiss the modal" class="modal-close" data-dismiss="modal" role="button" tabindex="0">\'d7</a>\
